{{multiple image | footer = Armenian cross | width = 100 | image1 = Armenian_cross.png | alt1 = | image2 = Armcross.svg | alt2 = }} An '''Armenian cross''' is a symbol that combines a [[cross]] with a floral postament or elements. In the [[Armenian Christianity]] it was combined with the [[Christian cross]] and this design was often used for [[high cross]]es ([[khachkar]]) – a free-standing cross made of stone and often richly decorated.
